The context window is the maximum amount of text that a chat AI system can consider at one time, encompassing both your conversation history and the response it's currently generating.
When you're having a long conversation with ChatGPT or Claude, the system isn't actually remembering everything you've ever said—it's only looking at the most recent exchanges that fit within its context window, which might be 8,000, 32,000, or even 128,000 tokens depending on the model.
Once your conversation exceeds this limit, the system has to start 'forgetting' the earliest parts of the discussion to make room for new information, which is why you might notice that if you reference something from much earlier in a very long conversation, the AI sometimes seems to have lost track of it.
